It looks like every usage of this is of the form:
Object encodedY = key.getOther().get("y");
if (!(encodedY instanceof String)) {
    log.error("something about property being an invalid value");
    return Optional.empty();
}
if (isNullOrEmpty((String) encodedY)) {
    log.error("something the key not containing a required property");
    return Optional.empty();
}

I just added the extra detailed logging because it was easy.
I suggest we simplify this code to a method on the getter that tests if the value is a non empty string.  If it is not we return Optional.empty() otherwise we return the value.  Something like:
public Optional<String> getStringProperty(String name) {
    Object value = other.get(name);
    if (value instanceof String && !((String)value).isEmpty) {
        return Optional.of(value);
    }
    return Optional.empty();
}

